#: instructor-training/_episodes/24-practices.md:14
msgid ""
"We're almost done with our training!  At this point, we've covered many, many topics\n"
"around teaching and learning, especially in the context of Carpentries workshops."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/24-practices.md:17
msgid ""
"Carpentries instructors use a set of teaching techniques based on evidence from\n"
"educational research. We've talked about some of these techniques explicitly\n"
"(e.g. participatory live coding and formative assessment), and others we've been modeling throughout\n"
"the workshop, without necessarily calling attention to what we were doing. Some of\n"
"these teaching techniques are implemented at particular points in a workshop, while\n"
"others are used throughout. Let's put together everything we've learned and organize\n"
"these practices in terms of what parts of a workshop we need to be conscious of each\n"
"of these strategies. In other words, let's put down on paper some of our mental model\n"
"about teaching and learning, specifically in the Carpentries context.  "
msgstr ""

